result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathan M Sherman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jonathan M Sherman in court with attorney Nicholas Abts. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Both files heard: 15CM390, 16CM43

Atty Constable makes statements to the Court.  
BY THE COURT:  Warrant in 16CM43 is quashed. 

State files Statement of Uncharged Read-in. 
Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CM390 Count 2 - NO CONTEST 
16CM43 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 15CM390 Count 2 & 16CM43.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
15CM390 Count 1 is dismissed and read-in. 
Court accepts the Statement of Uncharge Read-ins. 

Atty Constable makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Abts makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
15CM390 Count 2 - 
60 days jail - STAYED -
1 day credit.
Huber for work, counseling or any reason the sheriff will allow. 
Allowed to serve the 2nd half on electronic monitoring if he qualifies for that. 
12 months probation: 
OBtain  AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
Maintain absolute sobriety. 
Not possess any dangerous weapons. 
Provide a DNA sample. 
Pay the DNA surcharge. 
Pay $50 blood draw fee. 
Pay all other court costs including the Domestic Abuse surcharge. 
Participate in any other assesment or counseling deemed appropriate

16CM43;
60 days jail - STAYED -
Huber for work, counseling or any reason the sheriff will allow. 
Allowed to serve the 2nd half on electronic monitoring if he qualifies for that.
12 months probation: 
Comply with terms of probation in 15CM390. 
Pay costs including the DNA Surcharge.
